Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and @mayonnaise{32%g}. Set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lemon{1/2} and cut into wedges.

In another small bowl, combine the garlic, lemon zest, @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%g} and @olive oil{2%tbsp}(for the dressing). Set aside to add to the potatoes later.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Using the back of a #spoon{}, spread some sun-dried tomato mayo on top of the salmon fillet (reserving most for later), then press the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} on top. Drizzle with oil and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Halve the @premium tomato mix{125%g} and pop them onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil, then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel, then place it on the salmon baking tray.

When the potatoes have ~{10-15%minutes} left, remove them from the oven.

Drizzle with the parmesan, garlic and lemon oil, then toss to coat. Roast for the remaining ~{10-15%minutes} until crispy and golden.

At the same time, put the salmon tray on the middle shelf to bake until the salmon is cooked through and tomatoes have softened, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

While everything roasts, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat. Add the beans and cook until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{}.

Add the @butter{10%g} to the (now empty) pan on low heat. Season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and a squeeze of lemon juice.

Once the butter has melted, remove from the heat. Add the cooked green beans to the pan and toss to coat.

When everything's ready, transfer the salmon to your plates. Share out the crispy potatoes, making sure to scrape up any crispy cheese from the baking tray.

Serve the buttery green beans and roasted tomatoes alongside your salmon and finish with a dollop of sun-dried tomato mayo.

Sprinkle over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish. Enjoy!